WEBVTT

00:00.467 --> 00:03.369
[ UP-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS ]

00:13.680 --> 00:16.582
<i>LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,</i>
<i>REX HILLIARD!</i>

00:16.584 --> 00:18.083
[ APPLAUSE ]
OH!

00:18.085 --> 00:21.286
THANK YOU, LADIES AND GENTLEMEN.
THANK YOU, THANK YOU.

00:21.288 --> 00:23.389
OH, WOW.
YOU'RE HURTING MY EARS.

00:23.391 --> 00:25.124
[ CHUCKLES ]

00:25.126 --> 00:27.893
I CAN'T TELL YOU HOW SPOOKED
I GET BY LOUD NOISES.

00:27.895 --> 00:29.795
[ HORN HONKING ]
WHY, JUST THE OTHER DAY --

00:29.797 --> 00:31.830
OH, HEY, YOU!

00:31.832 --> 00:34.166
IT'S FLAKE THE CLOWN, EVERYONE.

00:34.168 --> 00:35.667
HA HA HA.
[ APPLAUSE ]

00:35.669 --> 00:38.103
[ HORN HONKING ]
OKAY, OKAY.

00:38.105 --> 00:39.405
PUT A SOCK IN IT,
WILL YOU?

00:39.407 --> 00:40.939
[ WHISTLE! ]

00:40.941 --> 00:42.374
[ GROANING ]

00:42.376 --> 00:44.943
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
PHOO!

00:44.945 --> 00:46.178
I MEANT "CAN IT."

00:46.180 --> 00:47.880
[ WHISTLE! ]

00:47.882 --> 00:50.382
[ LAUGHTER ]

00:50.384 --> 00:52.351
NOW, THAT'S NOT
WHAT I MEANT EITHER!

00:52.353 --> 00:55.721
SAY, IS THIS
CHANDLER'S TOMATO SOUP?

00:55.723 --> 00:58.724
WHY, I JUST LOVE
CHANDLER'S TOMATO SOUP.

00:58.726 --> 01:00.025
WHETHER SERVED PIPING HOT

01:00.027 --> 01:02.161
OR ROLLED
INTO A LADYLIKE CIGARILLO,

01:02.163 --> 01:05.497
CHANDLER'S TOMATO SOUP
GOES WITH EVERY MEAL.

01:05.498 --> 01:06.565
[ HORN HONKING ]

01:06.567 --> 01:08.000
WHY, YOU --

01:08.002 --> 01:09.435
HEY, FETCH, BOY!

01:09.437 --> 01:11.804
[ WHISTLE! ]
[ PANTING ]

01:11.806 --> 01:13.572
FLAKE THE CLOWN, EVERYONE!

01:13.574 --> 01:16.275
[ APPLAUSE ]

01:16.277 --> 01:18.811
WELL, WE'VE GOT A HECK OF A SHOW
FOR YOU THIS EVENING.

01:18.813 --> 01:20.813
A LOT OF LAUGHS,
SOME MUSIC, DANCE,

01:20.815 --> 01:22.548
AND, OF COURSE,
ANOTHER INSTALLMENT

01:22.550 --> 01:26.518
OF OUR GROUNDBREAKING MEDICAL
DRAMA "THE CHILDRENS HOSPITAL."

01:26.520 --> 01:28.587
[ APPLAUSE ]

01:28.589 --> 01:31.924
SO SINK BACK INTO YOUR CHAIRS...

01:31.926 --> 01:33.225
WAIT A MINUTE.

01:33.227 --> 01:34.560
SPEAKING OF SINKING...

01:34.562 --> 01:38.063
[ UP-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS,
FOGHORN BLOWS ]

01:38.065 --> 01:40.799
[ BELL CLANGING ]
EVERYONE OFF THE SHIP.

01:40.801 --> 01:42.734
THE <i> TITANIC</i> IS SINKING.

01:42.736 --> 01:44.770
OH, AND THEY SAID
IT WAS UNSINKABLE.

01:44.772 --> 01:47.339
JUST LIKE A MAN,
TO LIE TO A WOMAN.

01:47.341 --> 01:48.640
MAYBE THE SHIP'S TRYING

01:48.642 --> 01:50.642
TO GET AWAY
FROM YOUR COOKING, EDITH.

01:50.644 --> 01:52.711
WOMEN AND CHILDREN
FIRST.

01:52.713 --> 01:56.448
HE SAID "WOMEN," EDITH,
NOT RUSTY OLD ANCHORS.

01:56.450 --> 01:58.884
HM.
WELL, HE ALSO SAID "CHILDREN."

01:58.886 --> 02:02.154
SO PERHAPS
YOU <i> SHOULD</i> COME, JOHN.

02:02.156 --> 02:04.389
EVERYBODY IN.

02:04.391 --> 02:05.491
COME ON NOW, JOHN.

02:05.493 --> 02:07.759
I'LL BE JUST FINE
RIGHT HERE.

02:07.761 --> 02:10.395
YOU WOULD CHOOSE
A SINKING SHIP OVER YOUR WIFE?

02:10.396 --> 02:15.067
IF YOU HAD A WIFE LIKE MINE,
YOU'D BE THANKING THE ICEBERG.

02:15.069 --> 02:16.869
OH, LEAVE HIM, CAPTAIN.

02:16.871 --> 02:19.271
I HAVE A LIST OF COMPLAINTS
I'D LIKE TO GO OVER WITH YOU.

02:19.273 --> 02:22.975
FIRST, THE PORTHOLE SILLS
IN OUR ROOM WERE TOO ROUND.

02:22.977 --> 02:25.043
ALL I SAW OUTSIDE
WAS WATER.

02:25.045 --> 02:28.013
THE SUN SET
ON THE WRONG SIDE OF THE BOAT.

02:28.015 --> 02:29.348
THEY USED THE --

02:29.350 --> 02:30.582
SAY, WHERE ARE YOU
OFF TO?

02:30.584 --> 02:31.650
MIND IF I JOIN YOU?

02:31.652 --> 02:32.918
BE MY GUEST.

02:32.920 --> 02:34.586
OF ALL THE...

02:34.588 --> 02:36.622
LET'S GO, EVERYONE.
WE HAVE SOME SINKING TO DO.

02:36.624 --> 02:38.323
MAYBE THE BAND'S
STILL PLAYING.

02:38.325 --> 02:40.259
HM!

02:40.261 --> 02:42.494
[ APPLAUSE ]

02:42.496 --> 02:45.097
HO HO HO HO.
VERY FUNNY.

02:45.099 --> 02:46.632
VERY FUNNY.

02:47.600 --> 02:52.104
BUT A LARGE NUMBER OF PEOPLE
DID, IN FACT, DIE ON THAT BOAT.

02:52.972 --> 02:54.473
WHAT'S THAT?

02:54.475 --> 02:58.844
"DEAR REX, STOP TALKING SO MUCH
AND GET TO THE DANCE NUMBER."

02:58.846 --> 03:00.712
[ Laughing ] WHY, YES.

03:00.714 --> 03:02.948
SEEMS I FOUND MYSELF
IN A LITTLE PICKLE...

03:02.950 --> 03:06.485
JUST LIKE THIS FELLOW
ON THE LOWER EAST SIDE.

03:06.487 --> 03:08.921
♪♪

03:10.290 --> 03:12.691
[ UP-TEMPO PIANO MUSIC PLAYS ]

03:12.693 --> 03:13.892
[ WOLF-WHISTLES ]

03:13.894 --> 03:16.028
PICKLES!
GET YOUR FRESH PICKLES HERE!

03:16.030 --> 03:18.830
SOUR AS A CLAM,
SWEET AS ICE!

03:18.832 --> 03:22.134
BITE 'EM, SUCK 'EM,
ROLL 'EM INTO A CIGARILLO.

03:22.136 --> 03:23.635
NO? HMM.

03:23.637 --> 03:25.170
♪ PICKLES, PICKLES ♪

03:25.172 --> 03:26.405
♪ THE FRUIT OF THE SEA ♪

03:26.407 --> 03:29.408
♪ SO WHY WON'T ANYONE
BUY 'EM FROM ME? ♪

03:29.410 --> 03:30.876
♪ THEY'RE FRESH,
AND THEY'RE HOT ♪

03:30.878 --> 03:32.344
♪ THEY'RE SMOOTH AS A PEARL ♪

03:32.346 --> 03:35.447
♪ IF ONLY I COULD SELL 'EM
TO A GIRL ♪

03:35.449 --> 03:37.983
HEY! A GIRL!
A REAL GIRL.

03:37.985 --> 03:40.485
I WONDER
IF SHE'S A PICKLE-LOVER.

03:40.487 --> 03:41.853
PICKLE, MA'AM?

03:44.023 --> 03:47.492
SOMEDAY, I'LL FIND HER --
A REAL PICKLE-LOVER.

03:47.494 --> 03:50.629
♪ WHEN I FIND MY PICKLE GAL ♪

03:50.631 --> 03:53.165
♪ I'LL SET HER ON MY KNEE ♪

03:53.167 --> 03:56.768
♪ I'LL SLIP A PICKLE
ON HER FINGER ♪

03:56.770 --> 03:59.571
♪ AND SAY ♪

03:59.573 --> 04:01.940
♪ "PLEASE MARRY ME" ♪

04:01.942 --> 04:04.376
HALF-EATEN PICKLE HALF OFF!

04:04.378 --> 04:06.945
OH.

04:06.947 --> 04:10.582
[ British accent ] ♪ I'M JUST
A LONELY PICKLE-LOVER ♪

04:10.584 --> 04:13.619
♪ LOOKING FOR MY GUY ♪

04:13.621 --> 04:16.588
♪ I DON'T THINK
IT'S JUST PICKLE FUMES ♪

04:16.589 --> 04:19.625
♪ THAT'S MAKING ME CRY ♪

04:19.627 --> 04:22.461
♪ I WANT A MAN WITH GHERKINS ♪

04:22.463 --> 04:25.297
♪ WHOSE STRENGTH
I CAN'T REBUKE ♪

04:25.299 --> 04:28.634
♪ WITH EYES
AS GREEN AS PICKLES ♪

04:28.636 --> 04:30.936
♪ AND WHOSE BURPS
SMELL LIKE A CUKE ♪

04:30.938 --> 04:32.604
[ GASPS ]
ARE YOU?

04:32.606 --> 04:35.140
YES! AND YOU?
YES!

04:35.142 --> 04:36.441
Both: WE'RE BOTH...

04:36.443 --> 04:37.676
PICKLE-LOVERS!

04:37.678 --> 04:41.079
♪ WE FOUND A PICKLE FAMILY ♪

04:41.081 --> 04:43.415
♪ OUR WEDDING WILL BE FINE ♪

04:43.417 --> 04:47.753
♪ I'LL BE FOREVER YOURS ♪

04:47.755 --> 04:56.628
♪ IF YOU'LL BE FOREVER "BRINE" ♪

04:58.464 --> 05:00.966
[ MUSIC ENDS, APPLAUSE ]

05:03.236 --> 05:06.772
OOH!
NOW,<i> THAT'S</i> A SOUR PICKLE.

05:06.774 --> 05:08.707
[ LAUGHTER ]
[ CHUCKLES ]

05:08.709 --> 05:10.575
BUT NOT QUITE AS SOUR
AS MY WIFE'S FACE

05:10.577 --> 05:13.245
WHEN SHE FOUND AN EMPTY
MILK BOTTLE IN THE ICEBOX.

05:13.247 --> 05:14.813
[ LAUGHTER ]

05:14.815 --> 05:17.249
I WAS SO BLAMMO'ed,
I DON'T REMEMBER FINISHING IT.

05:17.251 --> 05:19.785
I THREW UP
INTO OUR DAUGHTER'S DOLLHOUSE.

05:19.787 --> 05:21.620
BLAH! [ CHUCKLES ]

05:21.622 --> 05:24.523
I'M WHAT YOU CALL
A REAL ALCOHOLIC.

05:24.525 --> 05:25.557
[ LAUGHTER ]

05:25.559 --> 05:27.125
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

05:27.127 --> 05:29.761
IT'S TIME TO PUT ASIDE
THE LAUGHTER FOR A MOMENT,

05:29.763 --> 05:31.663
IF WE COULD.

05:31.665 --> 05:34.499
THREE WEEKS AGO, WE INTRODUCED
A SEGMENT ON THIS SHOW.

05:34.501 --> 05:37.202
WE COULDN'T HAVE IMAGINED
THE RESPONSE THAT WE GOT.

05:37.204 --> 05:39.738
YOU SEE,
OUR STOCK-IN-TRADE IS COMEDY,

05:39.740 --> 05:41.006
SO TO BE ABLE TO PERFORM

05:41.008 --> 05:43.642
SOMETHING SO INTENSELY DRAMATIC
FOR YOU,

05:43.644 --> 05:46.244
WELL, IT MEANS THE WORLD TO US.

05:46.246 --> 05:47.713
LADIES...

05:47.715 --> 05:53.318
GET THOSE HANDKERCHIEFS READY
FOR ANOTHER INSTALLMENT OF...

05:53.320 --> 05:54.720
"THE CHILDRENS HOSPITAL."

05:54.722 --> 05:56.588
[ MID-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS ]

06:00.293 --> 06:02.994
WELL,
ANOTHER SUCCESSFUL SURGERY.

06:02.996 --> 06:05.697
HEY, HOW MANY LIVES
DID WE SAVE TODAY, DOC?

06:05.699 --> 06:07.532
10? 11?

06:07.534 --> 06:08.533
12?

06:08.535 --> 06:10.135
13? 14?

06:10.137 --> 06:11.370
15? 16?

06:11.372 --> 06:13.271
HEY, PENNY
FOR YOUR THOUGHTS, DOC.

06:13.273 --> 06:14.272
SORRY, GLENN.

06:14.274 --> 06:16.208
I DON'T KNOW
WHERE MY MIND WAS JUST NOW.

06:16.210 --> 06:19.378
[ CHUCKLES ] MY GUESS --
WHEREVER NURSE SPRAT IS.

06:19.380 --> 06:21.713
SAY, GLENN, HOW DO YOU KNOW
WHEN YOU'RE IN LOVE?

06:21.715 --> 06:25.650
WELL, FOR ME, IT FEELS LIKE
I'M SWIMMING ON THE MOON.

06:25.652 --> 06:28.153
YEAH.
YEAH, THAT'S IT.

06:28.155 --> 06:30.689
MOON-SWIMMING.
THAT'S EXACTLY HOW I FEEL.

06:30.691 --> 06:32.257
HEY, GLENN,
YOU KNOW WHAT I JUST DECIDED?

06:32.259 --> 06:34.192
I'M GONNA MAKE
AN HONEST WOMAN OUT OF HER.

06:34.194 --> 06:37.629
HOW ABOUT THAT?
[ APPLAUSE ]

06:37.631 --> 06:39.564
YOU SON OF A SO-AND-SO.

06:39.566 --> 06:41.233
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

06:41.235 --> 06:43.468
I TELL YOU, GLENN,
I'M SO HAPPY RIGHT NOW,

06:43.470 --> 06:44.803
I COULD JUST BURST.

06:44.805 --> 06:46.605
MY GUTS WOULD SPILL OUT
ALL OVER THE PLACE,

06:46.607 --> 06:47.873
AND THEY'D BE
HEART-SHAPED --

06:47.875 --> 06:49.207
EVEN MY HEART,
WHICH, TECHNICALLY,

06:49.209 --> 06:50.842
ISN'T EVEN SHAPED
LIKE A HEART AT ALL.

06:50.844 --> 06:52.577
NO. IF ANYTHING,
IT'S FIST-SHAPED.

06:52.579 --> 06:54.212
[ CHUCKLES ]
LOVE IS IRONIC THAT WAY.

06:54.214 --> 06:56.481
YOU KNOW, YOU'RE A REAL FRIEND,
GLENN ROSENSWEIG.

06:56.483 --> 06:58.650
SAY, YOU EVER THINK
OF CHANGING YOUR LAST NAME

06:58.652 --> 06:59.818
SO IT DOESN'T SOUND
SO JEW-Y?

06:59.820 --> 07:02.087
DOCTORS,
WE'VE GOT AN EMERGENCY!

07:02.089 --> 07:03.789
SHE STARTED COMPLAINING
ABOUT A STOMACHACHE.

07:03.791 --> 07:06.024
SHE'S IN GOOD HANDS NOW,
MOM.

07:06.026 --> 07:07.626
BEST HANDS
IN ALL OF BRAZIL.

07:07.628 --> 07:08.860
THAT'S WHERE WE ARE.

07:08.862 --> 07:10.996
SALLY, CAN YOU TELL ME
WHERE IT HURTS?

07:10.998 --> 07:12.831
MY APPENDIX.
OH.

07:12.833 --> 07:14.232
IF I WERE A DOCTOR,

07:14.234 --> 07:15.967
I'D SAY SHE'S SUFFERING
FROM ACUTE APPENDICITIS.

07:15.969 --> 07:17.736
IT'S A SHAME
WOMEN CAN'T BE DOCTORS,

07:17.738 --> 07:19.604
BECAUSE YOU SOUND LIKE
YOU'D MAKE A GOOD ONE.

07:19.606 --> 07:21.339
OKAY, WE NEED
TO OPERATE IMMEDIATELY.

07:21.341 --> 07:24.576
OR EVEN SOONER.
NURSE, SCALPELS.

07:24.578 --> 07:26.077
A LITTLE MORE GAUZE,
PLEASE.
ALL RIGHT.

07:26.079 --> 07:27.479
MORE GAUZE.
UH-HUH.

07:27.481 --> 07:29.514
MORE GAUZE FOR ME NOW.
I'LL TAKE A LITTLE MORE GAUZE.

07:29.516 --> 07:31.416
ALL RIGHT.
AND THAT'S IT.
I'VE LANDED IT.

07:31.418 --> 07:33.285
HA HA!
HOT DOG.

07:33.287 --> 07:34.286
YOU DID IT, OWEN.

07:34.288 --> 07:35.921
I'VE ALWAYS BELIEVED
IN YOU.

07:35.923 --> 07:38.690
AND I'VE ALWAYS LOVED YOU,
NURSE LOLA SPRATT.

07:38.692 --> 07:41.860
OH! I LOVE YOU,
DR. OWEN MAESTRO.

07:41.862 --> 07:44.329
GET ME A SNORKEL AND FINS,
BECAUSE I'M MOON-SWIMMING.

07:44.331 --> 07:46.097
I MEAN, I FEEL LIKE
SOME SORT OF MOON FISH.

07:46.099 --> 07:47.466
OH!
SAY, LOLA...

07:47.468 --> 07:48.934
HMM?
...I'VE GOT SOMETHING
FOR YOU.

07:48.936 --> 07:51.536
[ GASPS ]

07:51.538 --> 07:53.004
[ MONITOR BEEPING RAPIDLY ]

07:53.006 --> 07:54.206
WHAT'S
THAT NOISE?

07:54.208 --> 07:55.607
HER BLOOD PRESSURE'S
DROPPING!

07:55.609 --> 07:58.210
QUICK, OWEN, TRY THAT
NEW SUTURING TECHNIQUE

07:58.212 --> 08:00.178
YOU WERE TELLING ME ABOUT
WHEN WE WERE FLY-FISHING

08:00.180 --> 08:02.113
AT YOUR BROTHER'S
SWISS CHALET IN ALSACE.

08:02.115 --> 08:04.282
I DON'T HAVE A BROTHER
IN THE SWISS VILLAGE OF ALSACE.

08:04.284 --> 08:06.785
[ GASPS ]
BUT GLENN DOES.

08:06.787 --> 08:08.820
[ AUDIENCE GASPS ]

08:08.822 --> 08:10.021
OH.

08:10.023 --> 08:12.090
OWEN, I --
WE -- WE...

08:12.092 --> 08:13.892
LOOK, PAL,
YOU HAVE TO BELIEVE US.

08:13.894 --> 08:15.260
IT WAS JUST ONE WEEKEND.

08:15.262 --> 08:16.595
ALBEIT, IT WAS
THE FOURTH OF JULY WEEKEND,

08:16.597 --> 08:17.996
SO IT WAS THREE DAYS.

08:17.998 --> 08:19.698
AND THE FOURTH OF JULY
DID FALL ON A TUESDAY.

08:19.700 --> 08:21.666
IT DID FALL ON A TUESDAY,
SO MAKE IT FOUR DAYS.
FOUR DAYS.

08:21.668 --> 08:23.568
AND THEN WE WERE THERE. WE SAID,
"LET'S STAY FOR WEDNESDAY."

08:23.570 --> 08:24.970
AND THEN
IT JUST DIDN'T MAKE ANY SENSE

08:24.972 --> 08:26.171
TO FLY HOME FOR TWO DAYS.

08:26.173 --> 08:27.305
SO WE STAYED
THE EXTRA WEEKEND.

08:27.307 --> 08:28.707
BUT YOU HAVE TO BELIEVE US --

08:28.709 --> 08:30.308
IT WAS
JUST ONE NINE-DAY WEEKEND.

08:30.310 --> 08:32.443
WOULD SOMEBODY
SAVE OUR DAUGHTER?!

08:32.446 --> 08:34.578
RIGHT.
SCALPEL.

08:35.347 --> 08:37.315
PUT THIS OVER HERE
AND THIS OVER HERE.

08:37.317 --> 08:39.017
AND DON'T MOVE THAT.
WHY WOULD I?

08:39.019 --> 08:40.784
AND THERE WE GO.
AND I LANDED IT.

08:40.787 --> 08:42.721
OH!
SHE'LL BE FINE.

08:42.722 --> 08:45.423
AM I IN HEAVEN?

08:45.425 --> 08:47.993
[ CHUCKLES ]
WE'RE DOCTORS, SALLY.

08:47.995 --> 08:49.194
WE DON'T BELIEVE
IN HEAVEN.

08:49.196 --> 08:50.395
WE BELIEVE IN <i> SCIENCE.</i>

08:50.397 --> 08:52.330
SO YOU'RE
IN SCIENCE HEAVEN.

08:52.332 --> 08:54.599
[ CHUCKLES ]

08:57.436 --> 09:02.507
YOU'RE A REAL HERO,
DR. ROSENSWEIG.

09:02.509 --> 09:04.442
[ GASPS ] OH!

09:04.444 --> 09:05.610
A REAL HERO.

09:05.612 --> 09:09.781
THEN WHY DO I FEEL
LIKE A HORSE'S HEEL?

09:09.783 --> 09:11.516
OWEN...

09:11.518 --> 09:14.085
PLEASE SAY SOMETHING.

09:14.087 --> 09:18.023
A MOMENT AGO, I WAS
GONNA GIVE YOU THIS, LOLA --

09:18.025 --> 09:20.158
A SHINY
DIAMOND ENGAGEMENT RING...

09:20.160 --> 09:22.127
A RING
THAT COULD CUT GLASS.

09:22.129 --> 09:24.262
AND DO YOU KNOW
WHAT "GLASS" RHYMES WITH?

09:24.264 --> 09:26.064
NO, OWEN. PLEASE.
YOU KNOW I HATE RHYMES.

09:26.066 --> 09:27.799
ALSACE!
NO.

09:27.801 --> 09:30.235
AND THIS --
"SNAKE IN THE GRASS"!

09:30.237 --> 09:31.036
OH!

09:31.038 --> 09:32.304
FISTS, GLENN.

09:32.306 --> 09:34.506
FISTS ALSO
ARE FIST-SHAPED...

09:34.508 --> 09:36.408
LIKE MY HEART USED TO BE.

09:36.410 --> 09:37.742
BUT NOT ANYMORE.

09:37.744 --> 09:41.346
NOW IT'S LIKE TWO HALF-A-FISTS,
BECAUSE IT'S BROKEN.

09:41.348 --> 09:42.414
[ SOBS ]

09:42.416 --> 09:45.350
OH!

09:45.352 --> 09:46.451
[ CRYING ]

09:46.453 --> 09:49.454
I HAVE NO RIGHT
TO CALL MYSELF A DOCTOR.

09:49.456 --> 09:53.258
I VIOLATED
THE MOST IMPORTANT OATH --

09:53.260 --> 09:55.594
FIRST...

09:55.596 --> 09:56.861
DO NO HARM.

09:56.863 --> 09:59.331
[ SOBBING ]

09:59.333 --> 10:01.166
[ APPLAUSE ]

10:01.168 --> 10:05.537
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,
"THE SHOW YOU WATCH" PLAYERS!

10:05.539 --> 10:08.039
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]
HA HA HA.

10:08.674 --> 10:11.643
MUSIC, DANCE, SINGING,

10:11.645 --> 10:15.013
AND RIB-SPLITTING,
GUT-BUSTING LAUGHS.

10:15.015 --> 10:16.781
OH!
[ LAUGHTER ]

10:16.783 --> 10:21.419
OH, FLAKE, I DIDN'T MEAN
<i>REAL</i> RIBS AND GUTS.

10:21.421 --> 10:22.887
[ APPLAUSE ]

10:22.889 --> 10:24.623
WELL, THAT'S OUR SHOW, FOLKS.

10:24.625 --> 10:27.092
WE HOPE YOU HAD
AS MUCH FUN AS WE DID.

10:27.094 --> 10:29.094
TUNE IN NEXT WEEK
FOR ANOTHER EPISODE

10:29.096 --> 10:30.428
OF "THE CHILDRENS HOSPITAL,"

10:30.430 --> 10:33.531
WITH BASEBALL LEGEND
UGLY JOE BOYD.

10:33.533 --> 10:34.733
[ LAUGHS ]

10:34.735 --> 10:36.067
♪♪

10:36.069 --> 10:39.471
HEY, WELL DONE, SIR.
WELL DONE. HA HA HA.

10:39.473 --> 10:41.406
<i>THANK YOU FOR WATCHING</i>
<i>"THE SHOW YOU WATCH,"</i>

10:41.408 --> 10:44.576
<i>WITH REX HILLIARD AND</i>
<i>"THE SHOW YOU WATCH" PLAYERS.</i>

10:44.578 --> 10:47.045
<i>TUNE IN NEXT WEEK</i>
<i>FOR MORE "SHOW YOU WATCH" FUN</i>

10:47.047 --> 10:51.650
<i>AND ANOTHER SPECIAL EPISODE</i>
<i>OF "THE CHILDRENS HOSPITAL."</i>

10:51.652 --> 10:53.752
<i>SPECIAL THANKS</i>
